China's mass vaccination program relied almost entirely on domestically produced inactivated vaccines (primarily Sinovac's CoronaVac and Sinopharm's BBIBP-CorV), which accounted for the vast majority of the over 3.4 billion doses administered by mid-2022. Foreign mRNA vaccines like Pfizer-BioNTech or Moderna were never approved for general use in mainland China, despite early negotiations and secured doses that largely went undelivered.

China knew better.
